import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu

# Define function to calculate median TPM values for WT replicates
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    print(f"Calculating median TPM for WT columns: {wt_columns[:3]}... ({len(wt_columns)} columns total)")
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

# Define function to read data and combine them into a single DataFrame with tissue and regulation information
def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        print(f"Processing file: {file} for tissue: {tissue}")
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        print(f"WT columns found: {wt_columns[:3]}... ({len(wt_columns)} columns total)")
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue
        df['regulation'] = regulation_type
        dfs.append(df[['ID', 'median_TPM', 'tissue', 'regulation']])
    return pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)

# Read and process files
downregulated = read_and_process_files("downregulated_genes_updated", "downregulated")
unregulated = read_and_process_files("unregulated_genes_updated", "unregulated")
upregulated = read_and_process_files("upregulated_genes_updated", "upregulated")

# Combine all data
all_data = pd.concat([downregulated, unregulated, upregulated], ignore_index=True)

# Plot jitter+violin plot with specified colors
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))

# Define color palette
palette = {'downregulated': 'blue', 'unregulated': 'grey', 'upregulated': 'orange'}

sns.violinplot(x='tissue', y='median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, scale='width', inner=None, palette=palette)
sns.stripplot(x='tissue', y='median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, dodge=True, jitter=True, alpha=0.4, palette=palette)
plt.yscale('log')
plt.xlabel('Tissue')
plt.ylabel('Median TPM (log scale)')
plt.title('Median TPM Distribution Across Tissues')
# Adjust legend to avoid duplicate entries
handles, labels = plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()
by_label = dict(zip(labels, handles))
plt.legend(by_label.values(), by_label.keys(), title='Regulation', loc='upper right')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Perform Mann-Whitney U test to compare median TPM values between unregulated and up/downregulated
for tissue in all_data['tissue'].unique():
    print(f"Tissue: {tissue}")
    tissue_data = all_data[all_data['tissue'] == tissue]
    
    unregulated_median = tissue_data[tissue_data['regulation'] == 'unregulated']['median_TPM']
    upregulated_median = tissue_data[tissue_data['regulation'] == 'upregulated']['median_TPM']
    downregulated_median = tissue_data[tissue_data['regulation'] == 'downregulated']['median_TPM']
    
    _, p_val_up = mannwhitneyu(unregulated_median, upregulated_median, alternative='two-sided')
    _, p_val_down = mannwhitneyu(unregulated_median, downregulated_median, alternative='two-sided')
    
    print(f"\tUnregulated vs Upregulated p-value: {p_val_up}")
    print(f"\tUnregulated vs Downregulated p-value: {p_val_down}")

import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu

# Define function to calculate median TPM values for WT replicates
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu

# Define function to calculate median TPM values for WT replicates
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

# Define function to read data and combine them into a single DataFrame with tissue and regulation information
def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue
        df['regulation'] = regulation_type
        dfs.append(df[['ID', 'median_TPM', 'tissue', 'regulation']])
    return pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)

# Read and process files
downregulated = read_and_process_files("downregulated_genes_updated", "downregulated")
unregulated = read_and_process_files("unregulated_genes_updated", "unregulated")
upregulated = read_and_process_files("upregulated_genes_updated", "upregulated")

# Combine all data
all_data = pd.concat([downregulated, unregulated, upregulated], ignore_index=True)

# Normalize median TPM by log10
all_data['log_median_TPM'] = np.log10(all_data['median_TPM'] + 1)

# Plot jitter and violin plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
palette = {'downregulated': 'blue', 'unregulated': 'grey', 'upregulated': 'orange'}
sns.violinplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, scale='width', inner=None, palette=palette)
sns.stripplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, dodge=True, jitter=True, alpha=0.4, palette=palette)
plt.xlabel('Tissue')
plt.ylabel('Log10 Median TPM')
plt.title('Log10 Median TPM Distribution Across Tissues (Violin Plot)')

# Adjust legend
handles, labels = plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()
by_label = dict(zip(labels, handles))
plt.legend(by_label.values(), by_label.keys(), title='Regulation', loc='upper right')

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Plot box and whisker plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.boxplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, palette=palette, showfliers=False)
sns.stripplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, dodge=True, jitter=True, alpha=0.4, palette=palette)
plt.xlabel('Tissue')
plt.ylabel('Log10 Median TPM')
plt.title('Log10 Median TPM Distribution Across Tissues (Box Plot)')

by_label = dict(zip(labels, handles))
plt.legend(by_label.values(), by_label.keys(), title='Regulation', loc='upper right')

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

    tissue_data = all_data[all_data['tissue'] == tissue]

    print(f"\tUnregulated vs Upregulated p-value: {p_val_up}")

import numpy as np
import glob

import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu

# Define function to calculate median TPM values for WT replicates
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

# Define function to read data and combine them into a single DataFrame with tissue and regulation information
def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue
        df['regulation'] = regulation_type
        dfs.append(df[['ID', 'median_TPM', 'tissue', 'regulation']])

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu
from statsmodels.stats.multitest import multipletests

# Define function to calculate median TPM values for WT replicates
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

# Define function to read data and combine them into a single DataFrame with tissue and regulation information
def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue
        df['regulation'] = regulation_type.capitalize()
        dfs.append(df[['ID', 'median_TPM', 'tissue', 'regulation']])
    return pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)

# Read and process files
downregulated = read_and_process_files("downregulated_genes_updated", "downregulated")
upregulated = read_and_process_files("upregulated_genes_updated", "upregulated")

# Combine all data
all_data = pd.concat([downregulated, upregulated], ignore_index=True)

# Normalize median TPM by log10
all_data['log_median_TPM'] = np.log10(all_data['median_TPM'] + 1)

# Function to add p-value annotations
def add_p_val_annotation(ax, x1, x2, y, p_val, h=0.02):
    p_text = f'p = {p_val:.2e}'
    ax.plot([x1, x1, x2, x2], [y, y + h, y + h, y], color='k')
    ax.text((x1 + x2) * .5, y + h, p_text, ha='center', va='bottom', color='k')

# Set the Seaborn context
sns.set_context("notebook", font_scale=1.25)

# Sort tissues based on name
sorted_tissues = sorted(all_data['tissue'].unique())
all_data['tissue'] = pd.Categorical(all_data['tissue'], categories=sorted_tissues, ordered=True)

# Calculate p-values for the comparisons
p_values = []
for tissue, group in all_data.groupby('tissue'):
    up_scores = group[group['regulation'] == 'Upregulated']['log_median_TPM']
    down_scores = group[group['regulation'] == 'Downregulated']['log_median_TPM']
    if not up_scores.empty and not down_scores.empty:
        _, p_value = mannwhitneyu(up_scores, down_scores)
        p_values.append(p_value)
    else:
        p_values.append(1)

# Apply multiple testing correction (e.g., Benjamini-Hochberg)
reject, corrected_p_vals, _, _ = multipletests(p_values, method='fdr_bh')

# Create plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.boxplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, palette={'Upregulated': 'orange', 'Downregulated': 'blue'}, showfliers=False)
sns.stripplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, dodge=True, jitter=True, alpha=0.4, palette={'Upregulated': 'orange', 'Downregulated': 'blue'})
plt.xlabel('Tissue')
plt.ylabel('Log10 Median TPM')
plt.title('Log10 Median TPM Distribution Across Tissues (Box Plot)')

# Adjust legend
handles, labels = plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()
by_label = dict(zip(labels, handles))
plt.legend(by_label.values(), by_label.keys(), title='Regulation', loc='upper right')

# Add p-value annotations for each tissue
positions = plt.gca().get_xticks()
position_map = {tissue: pos for tissue, pos in zip(sorted_tissues, positions)}

for (tissue, group), p_value in zip(all_data.groupby('tissue'), corrected_p_vals):
    if not group[group['regulation'] == 'Upregulated']['log_median_TPM'].empty and not group[group['regulation'] == 'Downregulated']['log_median_TPM'].empty:
        up_pos = position_map[tissue] - 0.2 # Adjust depending on position
        down_pos = position_map[tissue] + 0.2 # Adjust depending on position
        max_height = max(group['log_median_TPM'])
        add_p_val_annotation(plt.gca(), up_pos, down_pos, max_height, p_value, h=max_height * 0.1)

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import glob
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import mannwhitneyu
from statsmodels.stats.multitest import multipletests

# Define function to calculate median TPM values for WT replicates
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

# Define function to read data and combine them into a single DataFrame with tissue and regulation information
def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue
        df['regulation'] = regulation_type.capitalize()
        dfs.append(df[['ID', 'median_TPM', 'tissue', 'regulation']])
    return pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)

# Read and process files
downregulated = read_and_process_files("downregulated_genes_updated", "downregulated")
upregulated = read_and_process_files("upregulated_genes_updated", "upregulated")

# Combine all data
all_data = pd.concat([downregulated, upregulated], ignore_index=True)

# Normalize median TPM by log10
all_data['log_median_TPM'] = np.log10(all_data['median_TPM'] + 1)

# Function to add p-value annotations with full scientific notation
def add_p_val_annotation(ax, x1, x2, y, p_val, h=0.02):
    exponent = int(np.floor(np.log10(p_val)))
    mantissa = p_val / (10**exponent)
    exponent_str = f"{exponent}".replace('-', '\u207B').translate(str.maketrans('0123456789','\u2070\u00B9\u00B2\u00B3\u2074\u2075\u2076\u2077\u2078\u2079'))
    p_text = f'p = {mantissa:.2f} x 10{exponent_str}'
    ax.plot([x1, x1, x2, x2], [y, y + h, y + h, y], color='k')
    ax.text((x1 + x2) * .5, y + h, p_text, ha='center', va='bottom', color='k')

# Set the Seaborn context
sns.set_context("notebook", font_scale=1.25)

# Calculate mean log_median_TPM for upregulated and downregulated groups and sort tissues by the difference in means
mean_diff = all_data.groupby(['tissue', 'regulation'])['log_median_TPM'].mean().unstack()
mean_diff['difference'] = mean_diff['Downregulated'] - mean_diff['Upregulated']
sorted_tissues = mean_diff.sort_values(by='difference', ascending=False).index

# Convert 'tissue' to ordered categorical type
all_data['tissue'] = pd.Categorical(all_data['tissue'], categories=sorted_tissues, ordered=True)

# Calculate p-values for the comparisons
p_values = []
for tissue, group in all_data.groupby('tissue'):
    up_scores = group[group['regulation'] == 'Upregulated']['log_median_TPM']
    down_scores = group[group['regulation'] == 'Downregulated']['log_median_TPM']
    if not up_scores.empty and not down_scores.empty:
        _, p_value = mannwhitneyu(up_scores, down_scores)
        p_values.append(p_value)
    else:
        p_values.append(1)

# Apply multiple testing correction (e.g., Benjamini-Hochberg)
reject, corrected_p_vals, _, _ = multipletests(p_values, method='fdr_bh')

# Create plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.boxplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, palette={'Upregulated': 'orange', 'Downregulated': 'blue'}, showfliers=False)
sns.stripplot(x='tissue', y='log_median_TPM', hue='regulation', data=all_data, dodge=True, jitter=True, alpha=0.4, palette={'Upregulated': 'orange', 'Downregulated': 'blue'})
plt.xlabel('Tissue')
plt.ylabel('Log10 Median TPM')
plt.title('Log10 Median TPM Distribution Across Tissues (Box Plot)')

# Adjust legend
handles, labels = plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()
by_label = dict(zip(labels, handles))
plt.legend(by_label.values(), by_label.keys(), title='Regulation', loc='upper right')

# Add p-value annotations for each tissue
positions = plt.gca().get_xticks()
position_map = {tissue: pos for tissue, pos in zip(sorted_tissues, positions)}

for (tissue, group), p_value in zip(all_data.groupby('tissue'), corrected_p_vals):
    if not group[group['regulation'] == 'Upregulated']['log_median_TPM'].empty and not group[group['regulation'] == 'Downregulated']['log_median_TPM'].empty:
        up_pos = position_map[tissue] - 0.2 # Adjust depending on position
        down_pos = position_map[tissue] + 0.2 # Adjust depending on position
        max_height = max(group['log_median_TPM'])
        add_p_val_annotation(plt.gca(), up_pos, down_pos, max_height, p_value, h=max_height * 0.1)

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Define function to calculate median TPM values
def calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns):
    median_tpm = df[wt_columns].median(axis=1)
    return median_tpm

# Define function to read data and combine them into a single DataFrame with tissue information
def read_and_process_files(directory, regulation_type):
    files = glob.glob(f"{directory}/*_{regulation_type}_annotated_updated.csv")
    dfs = []
    for file in files:
        tissue = file.split('/')[-1].split('_')[0]
        df = pd.read_csv(file)
        wt_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('WT')]
        df['median_TPM'] = calculate_median_tpm(df, wt_columns)
        df['tissue'] = tissue
        dfs.append(df[['Gene.name', 'median_TPM', 'tissue']])
    return pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)
